description: A babysitting job goes bad when a demon takes over the baby.
name: Turn Of The Screwball
Don't Meet Me At The Fair

description: Nunzio is dead?! Lou Martin on trial for murder?! Plus, the return of those alien “masterminds” Zinnac and Yoof.
name: A Good Manslaughter Is Hard To Find

description: A parallel or alternate story line leaves Lou Martin dead and Zinnac empowered and deranged with destroying Earth in their super-human social studies project which leads another Lou to set means to intercept Zinnac and stop him from crushing other realities.
name: An Expiration Date With Destiny

description: Straight out of a parallel reality, Lou Martin is killed by Yoof and the source of his powers are lunged onto Zinnac that modifies his body and throws his moral compass down the toilet to rule Earth. The mainstream Lou Martin has a get-together in another parallel reality to debate using his powers for anything, until prophesy leads him to the junkyard to overtake the appearance of the evil Zinnac.
name: What The Hell Is Goin' On Here!!?

description: Is this the beginning of the end? Or the end of the beginning? The past and present collide in this latest adventure! Plus, will Val finally make her move?
name: Been There, Done That

description: Lauren sees the future. It’s a future where Val, Gecko, and Francis are whole lot different, but Lou is still the same. The problem is the world has followed his example. So who will be prepared or interested enough to face the ultimate terror?
name: The Beginning Of The Middle Of The End

description: Don’t miss the yawn-inspiring conclusion to Major Bummer. Four different version of Lou must unite to save the universe. Can the most uninspired hero save the day? Since there is not going to be an issue 16, the odds aren’t good.
name: Saving Time

description:
Overview

After she fails to eliminate the young Jedi Luke Skywalker, Mara Jade is dispatched to take down a crimelord who seeks to reestablish the criminal organization Black Sun. Little does she know that the Emperor's imminent date with death will change her life forever! Written by Timothy Zahn and Michael A. Stackpole, and illustrated by Carlos Ezquerra.

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

Under cover of an Imperial raid, Mara Jade infiltrates the headquarters of would-be Black Nebula overlord Dequc, and assassinates the criminal leader. But back on Imperial Center, she finds evidence that the person she shot was a stand-in, and that the real Dequc is still out there, and gunning for her!

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

In the wake of the Emperor's death at the hands of Luke Skywalker and Darth Vader, Mara Jade has been captured! Since her captor is one of only a handful who knows she is the Emperor's Hand, Mara knows she must escape quickly -- or die.

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

After the death of Emperor Palpatine, Mara Jade escapes from Imperial Center and throws herself headlong into the underground of the Empire's underworld. Though her master is dead, Jade must complete her final mission . . . even if it costs her life!

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

Fed up with being hunted by her enemies, Mara Jade decides it's time to become the hunter. First on her payback list: the evil Dequc, Black Nebula crime lord -- the man who survived her final assignment for the Emperor! Now, Mara must infiltrate his hidden base, take him down, and escape! Could she finally be in over her head?

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

Mara Jade has destroyed many enemies of the Empire in her time, and has always carried out her missions with forethought and skill. But an unforeseen variable is about to enter the scene of her final mission for her dead employer, and Mara knows that her own survival is second to getting the job done!

volume.name: Star Wars: Mara Jade - By the Emperor's Hand

description:
Overview

His world is one where a man's fate is dictated by a ruthless government based on the foundations of Nazi Germany. A world where those decreed racially or religiously impure are branded as less than human and experimented upon like laboratory rats. He wears the mark of shame and bears the scars of their genetic tampering. The government considers him less than nothing--the lowest of the low.

They're about to find out they're wrong.
The Mark continues his crusade against the military might of the dictatorship, but it takes a young girl to show the Mark the importance of "Hearts and Minds."
It's Lutzany vs. the U.S.A. for the worlds' Heavyweight Championship. But can the Archon be trusted to stage a fair fight? And what can The Mark do to prevent a publicity victory for his oppressors?
The Mark disrupts a televised execution, turning the tables on the Nazi-like government of Lutzany and the State's High Executioner!

The Archon has a new member on his anti-Mark squad--a former Nazi propaganda expert who has been brought in from South America. Even his friends begin to doubt the Mark when he is falsely accused of murder, and an army of gun-wielding "Marks" are captured on film while murdering civilians!
The secrets of the Arcon's parents and his birth are revealed, and as Steward's "anti-Mark" program moves into high gear the Mark finds himself battling Steward's elite "Werewolves"!
An adaptation of Dr. Jekyll And Mr. Hyde.
name: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde

description: An adaptation of The Hunchback of Notre Dame.
name: The Hunchback of Notre Dame
20,000 Leagues Under The Sea

description: Adapting H.G. Wells' seminal novel depicting a Martian invasion of the world, as seen through the eyes of a Victorian man who witnessed the initial Martian cylinder landing. The technologically advanced Martians devastate the human military that seek to stop their advance, and humanity's chance of survival seems slim, until the Martians are defeated by Earth bacteria, against which they have no resistance.
name: War of the Worlds

description: Adapting Alexandre Dumas' epic tale of revenge, as Edmond Dantes is wrongfully imprisoned in a hellish gaol, only to finally escape after more than twenty years and, armed with a fortune gifted to him by a fellow prisoner, to return home using the new identity of the Count of Monte Cristo to avenge himself on those who framed him.
name: The Count of Monte Cristo

description: When unexplained phenomena begin occuring across the United States, federal police inspector John Strock investigates and discovers that Robur the Conqueror, self-styled Master of the World, is responsible.
name: Master of the World

description: Adapting H.G.Wells' science fiction tale, The Food of the Gods and How It Came To Earth. Hoping to find a solution to world hunger, scientists develop a substance that allows immature farm animals to reach gigantic sizes as they grow to adulthood, but it gets into the food chain, creating dangerous giant vermin.
name: Food of the Gods

description:
It's holiday stocking stuffer from the folks at Bongo. A Scrooge-like Itchy gets a wake-up call from a ghostly visitor and is determined to change his ways...especially towards the chronic victim of his malicious mischief...Scratchy. However, Scratchy is not in such a forgiving mood and there'll will be little peace on Earth until he gets his revenge on Itchy!

Note: The indicia title is "Itchy & Scratchy Comics #4".
name: It's A Wonderful Knife

description: Omaha has separation issues.
A move to a new place goes well.
Omaha works on her modeling career.
Omaha is confronted and threatened by a powerful adversary.
